ğŸ‘‰ Listing files and Directories 

ğŸ”¹ List Files: hadoop fs -ls /path 
ğŸ”¹ List Recursively: hadoop fs -ls -R /path
ğŸ”¹Sort by time: hadoop fs -ls -t /path
ğŸ”¹Search by Pattern: hadoop fs -ls / | grep *pattern*

ğŸ‘‰ Creating a New Directory

ğŸ”¹Create Directory: hadoop fs -mkdir /user/hadoop/dir
ğŸ”¹Create Directory Hierarchy: hadoop fs -mkdir -p /user/hadoop/dir1/dir2

ğŸ‘‰ Removing Files or Directories

ğŸ”¹Remove File: hadoop fs -rm /user/hadoop/file
ğŸ”¹Remove Directory: hadoop fs -rm -R /user/hadoop/dir

ğŸ‘‰ Copying Files

ğŸ”¹From Local to HDFS: hadoop fs -put /local/file /hdfs/dir
ğŸ”¹From HDFS to Local: hadoop fs -get /hdfs/file /local/dir

ğŸ‘‰ File Permissions

ğŸ”¹ Change file permissions: hadoop fs -chmod 755 /file_path 
ğŸ”¹ Change owner: hadoop fs -chown user:group /file_path

ğŸ‘‰ Viewing File Contents

ğŸ”¹View Last 10 Lines: hadoop fs -tail /hdfs/file
ğŸ”¹View First 10 Lines: hadoop fs -head /hdfs/file

ğŸ‘‰ Managing Files in HDFS

ğŸ”¹Copy Files: hadoop fs -cp /hdfs/file /new/hdfs/dir
ğŸ”¹Move/Rename Files: hadoop fs -mv /hdfs/file /new/hdfs/dir

ğŸ‘‰ Check Disk Space

ğŸ”¹Free Disk Space: hadoop fs -df -h /path
ğŸ”¹Disk Usage: hadoop fs -du -h /path

ğŸ‘‰ Replication Factor

ğŸ”¹Set File Replication: hadoop fs -setrep -w 2 /file
ğŸ”¹Set Directory Replication: hadoop fs -setrep -R -w 2 /dir

ğŸ‘‰ Compression
ğŸ”¹Read Compressed File: hadoop fs -text /file.gz

ğŸ‘‰ List Snapshots
ğŸ”¹List All Snapshots: hdfs dfs -lsSnap /path

ğŸ‘‰ Trash Operations
ğŸ”¹Empty Trash: hadoop fs -expunge

ğŸ‘‰ Snapshot Management

ğŸ”¹Create Snapshot: hdfs dfs -createSnapshot /dir
ğŸ”¹Delete Snapshot: hdfs dfs -deleteSnapshot /dir snapshot_name

ğŸ‘‰ Find Files Larger than X Size
ğŸ”¹Find Files Over 100MB: hadoop fs -find / -size +100M
